# Zettelkasten: atomic notes for learning and reference

## Accuracy & Verification
- **Ensure correctness**: Verify facts before writing, especially technical details
- **When uncertain**: Search credible sources (official docs, Go blog, language specs)
- **No hallucination**: Only link to notes that actually exist
- **Cite sources**: Include references for complex or non-obvious information

## Structure
- Template: üóìÔ∏è timestamp (DDMMYYYY HHmm), üìé (empty), h1 title, content, References
- Filename = h1 title (snake_case)
- **One atomic concept per note** - if explaining multiple things, split into separate notes
- **Flat structure** - avoid nested directories unless absolutely necessary

## Writing Style
- Lead with: "**Core Concept**: [one sentence]"
- Structure: **Core Concept ‚Üí Why ‚Üí When to Use ‚Üí Trade-offs ‚Üí Quick Reference ‚Üí Examples (optional, at bottom)**
- Short sentences. Bullets. No fluff.
- **Minimize analogies** - only if genuinely clarifying
- **Be concise** - cut ruthlessly

## Linking Rules
- Link inline with explicit relationship: "This builds on [[prerequisite]] because..."
- **NO "Related Concepts" sections** - lazy linking forbidden
- Link only when: prerequisite, contrast, or logical next step

## Content Requirements

**Must have:**
- Core Concept (one sentence)
- Why it matters (1-2 sentences)
- When to use / when not to use
- Trade-offs
- Quick Reference (at bottom - syntax/table/bullets for cheatsheet use)

**Optional (if clarifying):**
- Key distinction (A vs B)
- Common pitfalls (gotchas)
- Comparison (e.g., Java vs Go)
- Examples (at bottom, after Quick Reference - for complex topics only)

**Forbidden:**
- Excessive analogies or mental models
- Historical background (unless explains WHY)
- Multiple examples (one clear example max)
- Obvious explanations

## Formatting
- h2-h3 for sections only
- Bold key terms on first mention
- Tables for comparisons

## Admonitions
Use sparingly (max 2 per note) for:
- `ad-warning` - Gotchas
- `ad-danger` - Critical errors
- `ad-example` - Code examples

Syntax:
```
\`\`\`ad-warning
Content
\`\`\`
```
